body:
Geopolitical/administrative regions should be available from something like [GADM ](http://www.gadm.org/), [FAO GAUL](http://www.fao.org/geonetwork/srv/en/metadata.show?id=12691), or ISO19139 (e.g. ).

If no RDF is available, this may need to be created.
Note that ENVO [has some of these](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_00000004), but may not be up-to-date. SDGIO could use these too. 

@marieALaporte @elizabetharnaud @cmungall Do you think we should manage an OBO semantic version of this in ENVO and link to classes in, e.g., GAUL? Or should we go entirely with an external reference? GAUL looks pretty good as it maps to time stamped shapefiles that are relevant to the ag domain. 

@brianjlowe FYI

@celineaubert is beginning to create subsets using the `in_subset` AP. We should start exporting these for easy consumption by developers. Our recipe from ENVO (which will be a bit different from what we need here) is summarised below:
- First, we create a "simple" version of the ontology as a sort of subset in itself using owltools. The Makefile drives this [here](https://github.com/EnvironmentOntology/envo/blob/master/src/envo/Makefile#L42-L47). We should try to avoid the need to create an OBO version ([here](https://github.com/EnvironmentOntology/envo/blob/master/src/envo/Makefile#L59-L61)) and make the point below only rely on the simplified OWL file. @cmungall is that possible?
- With the basic file (currently an OBO file in ENVO), we can use owltools' subset extraction to pull out named subsets. See [these lines](https://github.com/EnvironmentOntology/envo/blob/master/src/envo/Makefile#L184-L191)

@marieALaporte, perhaps you could try to implement this?
